TY  - JOUR
AU  - Luo, Jiang
AU  - Subrahmanyam, Avanidhar
AU  - Titman, Sheridan
T1  - Momentum and Reversals When Overconfident Investors Underestimate Their Competition
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa016
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
SP  - 351
EP  - 393
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We develop a model in which overconfident investors overestimate their own signal quality but are skeptical of others’ Investors who are initially uninformed believe that early-informed investors have learned little, leading the former investors to provide excess liquidity, which, in turn, causes underreaction and short-run momentum. Skeptical investors can also react to stale information, causing momentum, followed by reversals. Hence, skepticism generates both momentum and reversals; the latter are amplified if investors overassess their own signal precision. We explain how long-run reversals can disappear while shorter-term momentum prevails, provide empirical implications, and link momentum to liquidity and price efficiency.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa016
ER  - 



