TY  - JOUR
AU  - Dessaint, Olivier
AU  - Olivier, Jacques
AU  - Otto, Clemens A
AU  - Thesmar, David
T1  - CAPM-Based Company (Mis)valuations
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhaa049
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 34
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 66
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - There is a discrepancy between CAPM-implied and realized returns. Using the CAPM in capital budgeting—as recommended in textbooks—should thus have real effects. For instance, low beta projects should be valued more by CAPM users than by the market. We test this hypothesis using M&amp;A data and show that bids for low-beta private targets entail lower bidder returns. We provide further support by testing several ancillary predictions. Our analyses suggest that using the CAPM when valuing targets leads to valuation errors (relative to the market’s view) corresponding on average to 12% to 33% of the deal values.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhaa049
ER  - 



